  2. #include "cspec/config.h"
  3. #include "cspec/core.h"
  4. #include <stdio.h>
  5. #include <string.h>


  8. DESCRIBE(strcmp, "int strcmp ( const char * str1, const char * str2 )") {

  10.     IT( "returns 0 only when strings are equal" )
  11.         SHOULD_EQUAL( strcmp("hello", "hello"), 0)
  12.         SHOULD_NOT_BE_NULL( strcmp("hello", "world") )
  13.     END_IT

  15.     IT( "returns a negative integer when str1 is less than str2"  )
  16.         SHOULD_BE_TRUE( strcmp("hello", "world") < 0 )
  17.         SHOULD_BE_TRUE( strcmp("0123", "1321431") < 0 )
  18.     END_IT

  20.     IT( "returns a positive integer if str1 is greater than str2"  )
  21.         SHOULD_BE_TRUE( strcmp("yellow", "world") > 0 )
  22.         SHOULD_BE_TRUE( strcmp("9", "789") > 0 )
  23.     END_IT

  25. } END_DESCRIBE;

  31.     CSpec_Run( DESCRIPTION( strcmp ), CSpec_NewOutputUnit() );
